The paper proposes a novel code search tool that uses natural language queries and crowdsourced knowledge from Stack Overflow to mine relevant API classes and code snippets from GitHub. This involves techniques from software engineering (cs.SE) such as code search and mining, information retrieval (cs.IR) for translating natural language queries into relevant API classes, natural language processing (cs.CL) for understanding the meaning of the query, machine learning (cs.LG) for ranking the results, and cybersecurity (cs.CY) for ensuring the security of the open-source projects being searched.
